The paper proposes a statistical test for determining whether two joint distributions are statistically different, which is relevant to machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also uses kernel methods and probability theory, which are relevant to cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.IT (Information Theory), respectively.
